S . Korea drafts insurance sector liberalising plan . South Korea has drafted a plan to allow the nation ' s top five business conglomerates , or " chaebol " , to participate in the life insurance sector , the Finance and Economy Ministry said on Tuesday . A ministry statement said the government also planned to permit banks , securities houses , private firms and individuals to set up insurance firms . LG and Sunkyong groups to join the Samsung Group in the sector sometime this year . Currently , Samsung is the only major chaebol which has a life insurance company under its wing . The ministry said entry into the insurance business by banks , securities firms and others was proposed for next month . The draft proposal has been presented to a ministry committee for approval in the near future , the statement said . The statement did not give further details . - - Seoul Newsroom ( 822 ) 727 5644 
